Azure Identity Services provide authentication and authorization mechanisms to securely manage access to Azure resources.

The core service is Microsoft Entra ID (formerly Azure Active Directory), which handles user identities, groups, and roles.

It supports:

* User authentication
* Single Sign-On (SSO)
* Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA)

For example, employees can log in once and access multiple applications.

A real-life use case is enterprise organizations managing thousands of user accounts securely.

Another example is SaaS applications using centralized identity management.

Identity services ensure secure access control across cloud resources.
